Package controllerGui

Class ReportSelectionController

  • java.lang.Object
    • controllerGui.ReportSelectionController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IScreen
    public class ReportSelectionController
extends java.lang.Object
implements IScreen
    Controller for the Orders Report screen. Handles displaying the order data in a pie chart and a bar chart. Allows switching between displaying the data by profit or by quantity.
    Author:
    David

    • Method Detail

      • viewReport

        void viewReport​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        This method is responsible for handling the event of the 'View Report' button being clicked. It validates the user input, and based on the selected report type, it sets the report data and opens the relevant report screen.
        Parameters:
        event - the event of the 'View Report' button being clicked

      • checkReportData

        private void checkReportData​(boolean RecievedData,
                             enums.ScreensNamesEnum screen)
        This method is used to check if the report data has been recieved from the server and to display the relevant report screen if the data is available.
        Parameters:
        RecievedData - a boolean variable indicating whether the report data has been recieved from the server or not
        screen - the screen that represents the report type that the user selected

      • initialize

        public void initialize()
        Initialize method is used to set the values for the different fields in the UI. It creates an ObservableList of years from 2016 to 2023. It creates an ObservableList of months from January to December. It creates an ObservableList of regions from DataStore. It calls setReportButtons method to set the action for each report button. It sets the items for the yearItemsCmb, monthItemsCmb and regionCmb with the created ObservableLists. If the connected user is a CEO, it enables the region selection otherwise it sets the region to the user's region.
        Specified by:
        initialize in interface IScreen

      • setReportButtons

        private void setReportButtons()
        This method is used to set the action for each report button. It assigns a different selectedReport variable for each button. supplyReportBtn sets "supplyReport", ordersReportBtn sets "ordersReport", clientReportBtn sets "clientsReport"

      • getSelectedReport

        private java.lang.String getSelectedReport()
        This method is used to get the selected report. It returns the selectedReport variable.
        Returns:
        the selected report as a string
